Boil a #pot{} of salted @water{} for the pasta.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Trim the @courgette{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Cut the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Cook the @dried rigatoni{180%g}, covered, for ~{12%mins}. Then drain and let it steam without the lid.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Heat a pan on high heat (no oil). When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%mins} total. Transfer the courgette to a #bowl{}.

Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the onion for ~{2%mins}.

Add tomato and fry for ~{5-6%mins}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cut the @Greek style cheese{100%g} into ½ cm cubes and tear the @basil leaves{5%g} into small pieces.

Add the pasta and the @green pesto{30%g} to the pan and heat for ~{1%min}.

Carefully toss the courgettes into the pasta.

In a large bowl, mix together the @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet} and 1 tbsp oil (double for 4p).

Season with salt and pepper.

Toss the @salad leaves{40%g} in the dressing.

Divide the salad leaves and pasta between your plates.

Garnish the dish with the Greek style cheese and basil.